<h1 class="ds-page-title">COMPASS Design System</h1>
<p class="ds-page-lead">
    A comprehensive guide to building consistent, accessible, and user-friendly interfaces across COMPASS. 
    This design system provides the building blocks, patterns, and guidelines needed to create cohesive user experiences.
</p>

<h2>About this design system</h2>
<p>
    The COMPASS design system ensures consistency across all features and pages. It provides:
</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Styles</strong> - Typography, colours, layouts, and formatting guidelines</li>
    <li><strong>Components</strong> - Reusable UI components with code examples</li>
    <li><strong>Patterns</strong> - Common interaction patterns and workflows</li>
    <li><strong>Accessibility</strong> - Guidelines for creating accessible interfaces</li>
</ul>

<h2>Getting started</h2>
<p>
    When creating new pages or features in COMPASS, refer to this design system to ensure consistency. 
    Each section provides examples, code snippets, and best practices.
</p>

<h3>Quick links</h3>
