<h2>Design principles</h2>
<p>
    The COMPASS design system is built on the following principles:
</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Consistency</strong> - Use the same components and patterns across all features</li>
    <li><strong>Accessibility</strong> - Ensure all users can access and use COMPASS effectively</li>
    <li><strong>Clarity</strong> - Make information easy to understand and actions easy to complete</li>
    <li><strong>Efficiency</strong> - Help users complete tasks quickly and accurately</li>
</ul>

<h2>Using this design system</h2>
<p>
    When building new features or pages:
</p>
<ol>
    <li>Review the relevant sections of this design system</li>
    <li>Use the provided components and patterns</li>
    <li>Follow the accessibility guidelines</li>
    <li>Maintain consistency with existing COMPASS pages</li>
    <li>Test with keyboard navigation and screen readers</li>
</ol>
